Madrin: Alright, thanks for staying up late and talking with us at Stratics. Could you please introduce yourself and your guild?<br>
Grenouille: Sure ! My name is Grenouille Bleue, and I'm the leader of the - mostly - European guild: The Frost Horde. The Frost Horde is a gathering of likeminded players who wish to play northerners in the Shadowbane World. This includes barbarians (of course), bards/scalds, warriors of all types, some channelers, runecasters... <br>
Grenouille:...we also have some less typical class, but they all have a roleplayed reason to have joined us. We have a fallen knight, a renegade prelate, a lusting-for-power templar... who all joined the Horde for these different reasons despite not being northerners. <br>
<br>
Grenouille: In Shadowbane, we *do not* plan to be an empire<br>
Grenouille|TFH dramatically stops here<br>
<br>
Grenouille: Our mottos are way more wordly. Our first and main goal is to establish ourselves in the uppermost city, no matter what the cost. This part is considered &quot;pre-roleplay&quot; for us, hence we'll accept all alliances, sell our souls and swords, whatever, to get it. Once we get this town (and, remember, we'll have it)...<br>
Grenouille: ..we'll just do what northerners are well-known for: plunder... and destroy... and pillage... and raid... and plunder. To make a long story short, become a nuisance to be reckoned. <br>
Grenouille|TFH sips some hydromel and awaits the next questions<br>
<br>
Madrin: What's your big plan for Shadowbane, after you get the guild settled in and all? <br>
Grenouille: Like I told you, we have no real dreams of being an empire. We let this for the softlanders. They work, we plunder. <br>
Grenouille|TFH grins<br>
Grenouille: Actually...Once the guild is settled, we'll try to secure our hometown and raid from there. All further sieges won't lead to us extending our dominion. We'll plunder what can be taken, kill those who didn't flee, then set the town to fire (thanks to collateral damage) and retreat. We actually hope to become *cough* more than a minor threat to more peaceful neighbourhoods, and a single hometown is way easier to defend anyway, especially in the North. <br>
<br>
<br>
Madrin: Care to let in those not in the know (like me) about your infamous hydromel? :-) <br>
