Madrin: What if the world is round? <br>
Grenouille: ahh, good question Madrin<br>
Grenouille: If the world is round... we'll have to advise. No better answer, I'm sorry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  However, even if a world is round, a secluded town will always have the advantage when it boils down to defense. Besides, I believe it won't be an easy fight for those who want to wipe us... <br>
Grenouille: I think we can kick some butts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  And ours are too hairy to be kicked.<br>
Madrin: I suppose the foot would just slide right off, with all the ice frozen to your petootie. Do you plan to make any friends/alliances? <br>
Grenouille: We already have some alliances, mostly with French guilds, that might really set us as a force to be reckoned with. Friends? We might have friends, as well... But remember the motto of the Horde... <br>
Grenouille: Move with us, or Move from us... else, just get trampled. <br>
Grenouille: Most players in our Horde have pride enough that we will prefer painful defeats to destroying our ideals. <br>
<br>
Madrin: Is there anything about the Frost Horde that you want the Shadowbane community to know? <br>
Grenouille: Yup. The Winter will be harsh! We're all merry guys, but don't expect us to behave &quot;good&quot; in game. We won't behave at all... And everything that's on our way shall bend knee or die - actually, the bending knee thingy is so that you can behead them more swiftly. We won't have any mercy. If we die, then we'll die smiling, a mug in our left hand and an axe in the right one, chanting to Torvalt through bubbles of blood...but we'll make sure not to die easily. No, we're not good guys. <br>
Grenouille: I hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
